###############################################################################
# OBJECTIVE
###############################################################################
Apply touch-friendly sizing to all 9 screens. Replace any remaining ad-hoc
sizes with token-based values. Ensure ≥ 8px spacing between touch targets.

###############################################################################
# LESSON FROM S44 (DESIGN_SPRINT_GUIDE.md)
###############################################################################
# In S44, we applied glass styling BY SCREEN, which was slow and error-prone.
# In S45, T2+T3 update the COMPONENTS FIRST, so most screens auto-fix.
# T4 only catches screen-specific overrides and raw <button> elements
# that bypass the component system.
#
# Focus areas for T4:
# 1. Raw <button> elements that don't use <Button> component
# 2. Ad-hoc className overrides that set heights (h-8, h-10 etc)
# 3. Spacing between adjacent interactive elements
# 4. Scrollable lists with tappable rows (min-height)

