###############################################################################
# WHAT T4 SHOULD NOT DO
###############################################################################
anti-patterns:
  - ❌ Don't add h-12 to every element by hand — component defaults handle it
  - ❌ Don't change component internals — that was T3's job
  - ❌ Don't add new components — use existing Button, Input, GlassButton
  - ❌ Don't change visual design — only sizing and spacing

###############################################################################
# RAW BUTTONS TO CONVERT
###############################################################################
Raw <button> elements that bypass the component system (need conversion or sizing):
  1. objects-screen.tsx vehicle rows → add min-h-[3.5rem]
  2. tracking-screen.tsx vehicle select → convert to <Button variant="glass">
  3. select-objects-screen.tsx vehicle rows → add min-h-[3.5rem]
  4. mobile-shell.tsx tab buttons → add min-h-[3.5rem]
  5. login-screen.tsx show/hide password → ensure touch area via .touch-area

###############################################################################
# ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA
###############################################################################
verify:
  - [ ] Zero interactive elements below 44px measured touch target
  - [ ] All ad-hoc height classes (h-8, h-9, h-10) replaced with tokens
  - [ ] Spacing ≥ 8px between all adjacent touch targets
  - [ ] Raw <button> elements have proper min-height
  - [ ] pnpm run build && pnpm run lint pass with zero errors
  - [ ] Visual layout not broken (no excessive spacing gaps)
